Here is a simple CSS code to style a button with a bright green background and white text:
```
.button {
  background-color: #34C759; /* bright green */
  color: #FFFFFF; /* white */
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.button:hover {
  background-color: #2ECC40; /* darker green on hover */
}
```
You can apply this CSS to a button element in your HTML like this:
```
<button class="button">Click me!</button>
```
This will give you a button with a bright green background and white text. The `:hover` pseudo-class is used to change the background color to a darker green when the button is hovered over.

You can adjust the colors, padding, border radius, and other styles to your liking.

